# Create ADR (Project Overlay)

The full skill — ADR template, mandatory alternatives table, content discipline — is in the `praxis` plugin's `create-adr` skill. Read it first.

## Project-specific paths

- Durable architecture tree: `{{paths.architecture}}/` — system overview (`README.md`) and per-capability records (`<capability>/README.md`, the current-state truth).
- ADR home by decision altitude: `{{paths.architecture}}/<capability>/adr/` (capability-scoped) or `{{paths.adr}}/` (cross-capability).
- Filename + ID: follow the plugin's collision-safe `ADR.<ID>-<kebab-slug>.md` convention.
- Registration: add the ADR to the capability record's ADR index (or the system overview for a cross-capability decision).

## When an ADR is mandatory

- New top-level capability domain
- New external integration (third-party API, identity provider, payment processor, etc.)
- Storage schema changes that affect more than one capability
- Any change to auth flow or trust boundary
- Any change to the deployment topology
- Any decision a new contributor would otherwise have to reverse-engineer from code

## Project-specific gates

- Authored or owned by the principal engineer (`.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.principal_engineer}}.agent.md`).
- Must be referenced from the relevant wave's `product-architecture.md` if it was driven by wave work, and from the capability record it shapes.
- Status transitions (`Proposed` → `Accepted` → `Superseded`) update the ADR file and its index (capability record or system overview) in the same commit.
